<h2>Technical SEO Blogs</h2>
<p>Technical SEO is the foundation every other ranking factor depends on. These blogs have been recognized for their depth on crawlability, indexing, site speed, and structured data. They cover problems that general SEO blogs never surface. And solutions that move the needle on large sites.</p>
<p><strong>Screaming Frog Blog</strong>. Screaming Frog</p>
<p>The team behind the most widely used desktop crawler has produced some of the most thorough technical SEO documentation available. Their guides on log file analysis, crawl budgets, and site migrations go far beyond product tutorials. They are practical references for any technical SEO facing complex audit challenges. Essential reading before and after every site migration.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.screamingfrog.co.uk/blog/">screamingfrog.co.uk/blog</a></li>
<li><strong>X/Twitter:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/screamingfrog">@screamingfrog</a></li>
<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/screaming-frog">Screaming Frog</a></li>
<li><strong>Publishing Frequency:</strong> 2 to 3 times per month</li>
<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Crawl audits, site migrations, and technical SEO tutorials</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Botify Blog</strong>. Botify</p>
<p>Botify earned its reputation by solving crawl problems that most tools cannot even surface. Their blog covers crawl budget management, JavaScript rendering, and log file analysis at a scale that enterprise teams actually face. The insights here come from working with sites that have millions of indexed pages. A level of technical depth you will not find on general SEO blogs.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.botify.com/blog">botify.com/blog</a></li>
<li><strong>X/Twitter:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/botify">@botify</a></li>
<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/botify">Botify</a></li>
<li><strong>Publishing Frequency:</strong> Weekly</li>
<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Enterprise technical SEO and crawl budget optimization</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Lumar Blog</strong>. Lumar (formerly Deepcrawl)</p>
<p>Lumar has built a strong reputation for technical SEO research that goes beyond surface-level audits. Their work on JavaScript SEO, Core Web Vitals, and site architecture is backed by real crawl data from mid-to-large websites. For technical teams that need guidance on indexation and internal linking at scale, Lumar's blog is a consistent and reliable resource.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://lumar.io/blog/">lumar.io/blog</a></li>
<li><strong>X/Twitter:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/LumarIO">@LumarIO</a></li>
<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/lumar">Lumar</a></li>
<li><strong>Publishing Frequency:</strong> Weekly</li>
<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Site architecture, internal linking, and JavaScript SEO</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>ContentKing Blog</strong>. ContentKing (now part of Conductor)</p>
<p>ContentKing has pioneered the case for real-time SEO monitoring, and their blog reflects that forward-thinking approach. Rather than waiting for weekly crawls to surface issues, their guides teach proactive on-page monitoring, indexation change detection, and audit strategies that catch problems before rankings drop. An important voice for teams that cannot afford SEO surprises.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.contentkingapp.com/blog/">contentkingapp.com/blog</a></li>
<li><strong>X/Twitter:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/ContentKingApp">@ContentKingApp</a></li>
<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/contentking">ContentKing</a></li>
<li><strong>Publishing Frequency:</strong> 2 to 3 times per month</li>
<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Real-time SEO monitoring and on-page change detection</li>
